Title: Example import_mut_data
Description: Data frame object containing list of sequenced sites for sample dna00996.1. Used as an example for importing tabular datasets with MutSeqR.

Title: Example import_mut_data using Custom column names
Description: Data frame object containing list of sequenced sites for sample dna00996.1. Used as an example for importing tabular datasets with MutSeqR when dataset has custom column names.

Title: Example import_vcf_data
Description: Block compressed VCF file containing list of sequenced sites for sample dna00996.1. Used as an example for importing VCF datasets with MutSeqR.

Title: Example mutation data
Description: Data frame object containing list of sequenced sites for 24 samples. Unfiltered. Used as an example for filtering mutation data with MutSeqR.

Title: Example mutation data filtered
Description: Data frame object containing the filtered list of sequenced sites for 24 samples.  Used as an example for downstream MutSeqR functions.

Title: Precalculated Depth at Base 6 Resolution
Description: Data frame object containing the pre-calculated total depth values for each sample at 6-base subtype resolution. Used as an example in calculate_mf()

Title: Precalculated Depth at Base 12 Resolution
Description: Data frame object containing the pre-calculated total depth values for each sample at 12-base subtype resolution. Used as a reference for users.

Title: Precalculated Depth at Base 96 Resolution
Description: Data frame object containing the pre-calculated total depth values for each sample at 96-base subtype resolution. Used as a reference for users.

Title: Precalculated Depth at Base 192 Resolution
Description: Data frame object containing the pre-calculated total depth values for each sample at 192-base subtype resolution. Used as a reference for users.
